      "question": "In distributed data parallel training, what does each GPU do before synchronization?",
      "stem_format": "plain_text",
      "choices_format": "plain_text",
      "choices": [
        "It runs the same model on a different slice of data and computes gradients for that slice.",
        "It owns a different layer of the model and never stores the full model.",
        "It computes only optimizer statistics while another GPU computes gradients.",
        "It receives identical data so all activations and gradients are identical before communication."
      ],
      "answer_index": 0,
      "explanation": "DDP replicates the model and splits the data. Each worker sees different examples, so its local gradients differ until communication combines them into a shared update.",
